race.description: Daish Irrigation And Fodder Grade 5 Series F Pr1 D
race.comment: IS HE LUCKY (8) jumped from out wide and was game in defeat last start when a 1.1 lengths third (25.35) behind Got A Habit at Shepparton. Goes very well from this draw with 10 wins and six minor placings from 18 starts. Sure to be about the mark. IS HE HAPPY (2) was prominent throughout when an impressive winner two back but could manage only midfield last time when finished 6th and beaten 6 lengths at Shepparton (22.59). In the mix. TODD'S LUKA (1) stuck on well last time to finish a neck back in second (23.23) at Gawler in a Other over 400m. Has never been out of the placings from three starts out of this box. Hard to beat again. MINH JACK (7) has been in the frame at his last two runs, most recently when second (19.78) in a Grade 5 over 342m at Angle Park.
